cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.DS 

The paper introduces a method to train Binarized Neural Networks (BNNs) and conducts experiments on image classification tasks such as MNIST, CIFAR-10, and SVHN. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the reduction in memory size and power-efficiency achieved by BNNs, which suggests relevance to sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper includes a discussion of a binary matrix multiplication GPU kernel, which suggests relevance to sub-category cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
